<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.1.7 System Integrity and Failure Behavior

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section has no separate child file in the first root SRS. Detailed subsystem-specific failure behavior remains owned by the relevant child files.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-INT-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Runtime Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt shall remain the authoritative in-memory state for the current run. No other runtime object shall keep a parallel source of truth for the active prompt, selected context, memory context, stage state, or prompt-ready rendering.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-INT-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stage Failure Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
Stage failures shall not partially corrupt SuperPrompt state. Either a stage update is applied coherently, or the previous valid state remains available for inspection and recovery.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-INT-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Inspectable Context Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
Selected document context, selected memory context, stage views, final selection IDs, condensed context, and model-bound context shall remain inspectable rather than hidden inside model calls.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-INT-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Silent Deletions
STATEMENT: >>>
Documents, memory entries, vectors, histories, and selected context shall not be silently deleted or ignored except through explicit user control, file-change logic, or approved retention policy.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.1.8 Non-Goals and Current Boundaries

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section preserves explicit current non-goals so future child files do not accidentally promote them into active scope.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-NG-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Current Dynamic Multi-Agent Planner Goal
STATEMENT: >>>
The current requirements shall not define a full multi-agent planner that dynamically rewires the pipeline as a current goal.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-NG-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Full LangChain or LangGraph Replacement Goal
STATEMENT: >>>
The current requirements shall not define GHOST as a full-blown LangChain or LangGraph replacement. The documented direction is a custom tight architecture that may borrow good ideas without replacing its own design.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-NG-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Current Multi-Tenant Policy Engine Goal
STATEMENT: >>>
The current requirements shall not define complex policy engines for access control, user management, or multi-tenant cloud deployment as current scope.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-NG-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Reinforcement Self-Tuning Goal
STATEMENT: >>>
The current requirements shall not define automatic self-tuning of pipeline parameters through reinforcement learning as current scope.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2 Functional Requirements

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.1 Prompt Orchestration -> 10_prompt_orchestration.sdoc

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/10_prompt_orchestration.sdoc

This file shall later contain detailed requirements for preprocessing, A2 PromptShaper, SuperPrompt mutation, SuperPromptProjector rendering, A5 reserved direction, and final Prompt Builder/send-boundary behavior.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-PRM-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt Orchestration Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide prompt orchestration that turns free-form user prompts into structured SuperPrompt state and prompt-ready output through preprocessing, prompt shaping, controlled context assembly, and GUI-visible rendering.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-PRM-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Prompt Rendering Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
Current GUI-visible engineered prompt rendering shall be described as SuperPromptProjector and SuperPrompt prompt-ready composition behavior, not as completed dedicated Prompt Builder authority.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-PRM-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Prompt Builder Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The dedicated final Prompt Builder/send-boundary remains incomplete and shall be specified later before it is claimed as completed product behavior.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-PRM-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A5 and Hard Rules Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A5 and full Hard Rules behavior shall remain reserved, postponed, or placeholder behavior until their final controller action and enforcement semantics are approved in later requirements.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.2 Orchestration Controller

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section stays in the root SRS for now because the Controller connects many child capabilities. A separate child file may be added later if Controller requirements become too large for the root SRS.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-CTRL-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Controller Orchestration Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide an AppController that owns the active SuperPrompt for a session, manages active project context, calls each implemented pipeline stage in legal order, updates stage/history fields, and returns updated SuperPrompt state to the GUI.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-CTRL-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Executable Runner Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The current executable GUI runner shall be described as running through PreProcessing, A2, Retrieval, ReRanker or pass-through, A3, and A4, not as a completed full A0-to-Prompt-Builder target pipeline.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.3 Agent Stack -> 20_agent_stack.sdoc

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/20_agent_stack.sdoc

This file shall later contain detailed requirements for AgentFactory, AgentPrompt, llm_client, JSON agent definitions, structured output parsing, executable modes, aliases, model configuration, and stateless agent behavior.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-AGT-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: JSON-Defined Agent Stack
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide a neutral JSON-defined Agent Stack consisting of AgentFactory, AgentPrompt, and llm_client abstractions for implemented LLM-based stages and future specialist agents.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-AGT-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Executable AgentPrompt Modes
STATEMENT: >>>
The current executable AgentPrompt compose modes shall be described as selector, classifier, and synthesizer. Chooser and multi-chooser may be documented as aliases or design vocabulary. Writer and Extractor shall not be claimed as live compose modes without child requirements and code evidence.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-AGT-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: LLM Client Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
LLM-based stages shall access external model providers through the llm_client abstraction rather than direct provider calls from Controller or GUI code.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.4 Document Knowledge -> 30_document_knowledge.sdoc

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed parent child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/30_document_knowledge.sdoc

Proposed deeper child files:

- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/31_document_ingestion.sdoc
- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/32_document_retrieval.sdoc
- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/33_evidence_selection_and_condensation.sdoc

The root SRS only states the main elements of document knowledge. Detailed ingestion, retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4 requirements belong in those child files.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-DOC-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Knowledge Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide project document knowledge through project-scoped document ingestion, chunking, embeddings, sparse representations where enabled, vector stores, retrieval, document-only reranking, relevance filtering, and condensation.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-DOC-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Import Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The current document upload/import boundary shall be described as limited to .txt and .md files unless later requirements and implementation evidence extend supported file types.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-DOC-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hybrid Document Retrieval
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide deterministic project-aware document retrieval that combines dense retrieval and SPLADE sparse scoring in the documented hybrid retrieval path where the sparse branch is enabled.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-DOC-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document-Only ReRanker Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The ReRanker shall be described as operating on document retrieval results. Memory candidates shall remain separately represented in SuperPrompt and shall not be implied as part of the same reranked document candidate list.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-DOC-005
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Selection and Condensation
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide document evidence selection and condensation through ReRanker, A3 usefulness gating, A4 document-context condensation, final selection IDs, and GUI-inspectable stage views.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.5 Memory System -> 40_memory_system.sdoc

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed parent child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/40_memory_system.sdoc

Proposed deeper child files:

- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/41_memory_recording.sdoc
- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/42_memory_ingestion.sdoc
- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/43_memory_retrieval.sdoc
- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/44_memory_merge_and_activebrief.sdoc
- doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/45_memory_files_and_import.sdoc

Memory is intentionally the deepest proposed area because the existing project already separates durable memory truth, vector ingestion, retrieval, runtime compression/merge, ActiveBrief direction, and server-side memory-file management.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-MEM-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory System Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide a structured engineering memory system for durable memory records, metadata, indexing, vector ingestion, retrieval, compression, merge, ActiveBrief direction, and controlled reuse of prior engineering context.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-MEM-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Truth Split
STATEMENT: >>>
The memory system shall preserve the split between .ragmem stable memory body, .ragmeta.json editable metadata mirror, and SQLite query/index metadata.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-MEM-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Composite Retrieval Stage
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Retrieval stage shall be described as composite: document retrieval runs through the document path, and memory retrieval runs when MemoryRetriever is configured. Memory candidates shall remain separate from document candidates.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-MEM-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Merge and Open Final Policy
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory retrieval, runtime compression, and MemoryMerge synthesis exist, but final Direct Recall priority, memory-context inclusion policy, and final Prompt Builder/send-boundary behavior remain open until approved child requirements define them.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-MEM-005
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveBrief Relation Routing
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall preserve ActiveBrief relation classification as a root-level capability anchor because it affects memory retrieval direction and comparison-context construction. Detailed routing rules belong in child memory requirements.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.6 GUI Workbench -> 50_gui_workbench.sdoc

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/50_gui_workbench.sdoc

This file shall later contain detailed requirements for Streamlit GUI layout, workspace behavior, files tab, metrics tab, hard-rules placeholder, general settings placeholder, memory controls, runtime logs, upload limits, and prompt-only mode if approved.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-GUI-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: GUI Workbench Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide a human-facing Streamlit GUI workbench for prompt input, project selection, ingestion controls, pipeline execution, engineered prompt display, memory controls, runtime logging, file management, and inspection of system state.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-GUI-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: GUI Pipeline Controls
STATEMENT: >>>
The GUI shall expose controls for the implemented pipeline stages so the user can trigger and inspect stage-by-stage execution while the current runner remains bounded to the implemented stages through A4.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-GUI-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: GUI Placeholder Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
GUI elements for Hard Rules, Direct LLM Call, metrics/observability, prompt-only mode, Blackboard Actor, or future behavior shall not be described as completed product behavior unless supported by implementation evidence and approved child requirements.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-GUI-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt-Only Mode Proposal
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST may support a prompt-only mode in which document retrieval and memory retrieval are selectively deactivated and the system behaves as a prompt builder rather than a context generator. This is a proposal and shall require separate child requirements before implementation.
<<<

