[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.2.7 External Interfaces and AI Tooling Boundary

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section gives only root-level interface categories. Detailed API endpoints, exact GUI behavior, and deployment interface details belong in child files after approval.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-EXT-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: External AI Tooling Compatibility
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall support workflows where engineered prompts and selected context can be used with external AI tooling while keeping surrounding context construction, memory, rules direction, retrieval, and synchronization direction under GHOST control.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-EXT-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Direct LLM Call Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Direct LLM Call shall be treated as optional future send-boundary behavior or placeholder behavior until current code evidence and approved child requirements define it as completed.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-EXT-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Browser User Interface Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The current GHOST user interface shall be accessed as a browser-based Streamlit application in local and deployed runtime modes.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-EXT-004
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Network Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The deployed GUI shall be exposed through the documented AWS reverse-proxy and HTTPS path rather than treating internal application ports as public product interfaces.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-EXT-005
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: File System Interface Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall use documented project data directories and runtime data directories as controlled file-system interfaces for project documents, vector stores, memory files, manifests, logs, and persistent runtime data.
<<<

