[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/60_runtime_operations.sdoc

This file shall later contain detailed functional and non-functional runtime requirements for local execution, Docker, AWS, deployment activation, and operational troubleshooting.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-OPS-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Operations Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall support local development execution and AWS-compatible deployment through the documented Docker, ECR, EC2, nginx, HTTPS, Route53, SSM Parameter Store, and persistent runtime data path.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-OPS-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Persistence Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall preserve project data, memory data, vector stores, and runtime artifacts through a persistent runtime data path that remains outside the Docker image in deployed mode.
<<<

