[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Proposed child file:

doc/01-Requirements/strictdoc/80_requirement_traceability_direction.sdoc

This file shall later contain the controlled requirement-architecture-code-test traceability direction. It shall not invent detailed synchronization-agent implementation behavior before the human maintainer approves it.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-TRC-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirement Traceability Direction
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall preserve a future capability direction for deterministic traceability across requirements, architecture, code, and tests using stable IDs.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-TRC-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Future Synchronization Agent Usage Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A future synchronization agent may use stable requirement IDs and code-side UID markers to compare connected requirements, architecture, code, and tests, but actual modification of artifacts shall remain subject to human approval and later detailed requirements.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-TRC-003
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Current Automation Claim
STATEMENT: >>>
The root SRS shall not claim that automatic requirement-architecture-code synchronization is currently implemented unless that claim is supported by implementation-status evidence and approved detailed requirements.
<<<

